benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/admin/healthcheck - Put the host out of rotation

covered: DELETE method - Valid Deletion: 204 with empty body and host moved out of rotation (TC01).
Conflict/No Resources - Host already out of rotation or no hosts available: 409 responses (TC04, TC14).
Service Availability - 503 when service is down (TC05).
Server Errors - 500 Internal Server Error handling (TC06).
Method Not Allowed - 405 for invalid HTTP method (TC07).
Bad Request - 400 for invalid body or malicious payload (TC09, TC13).
Header Validation - Injection or malicious headers handling (TC13).
Extra Parameters Handling - 204 with extra query parameters (TC08).
Performance - Response time under normal load (TC10) and under concurrency (TC11).
Concurrency - Handling multiple concurrent DELETE requests (TC11).
gaps: Missing explicit 403 Forbidden case for insufficient privileges.
No explicit non-existent resource test beyond “no hosts in rotation” (e.g., deleting a non-registered host).
No tests for rate limiting/throttling on DELETE operations.
No tests for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) in responses.
Additional header validation edge cases (missing required headers) not covered.
recommendations: Add a dedicated 403 Forbidden test to cover insufficient privileges on delete.
Add tests for non-existent or unregistered hosts (404/409 as appropriate).
Introduce rate limiting tests to ensure throttle behavior under burst load.
Add caching behavior tests for DELETE responses if applicable (ETag/Cache-Control).
Add tests around header validation edge cases (missing required headers, invalid header formats).
Consider adding explicit race-condition tests for concurrent DELETE requests to strengthen concurrency coverage.
